'''Oguni Footslopes Kofun Group''' (雄国山麓古墳群, Oguni-sanroku Kofun-gun) is a group of four Kofuns located in [[:en:Kitakata, Fukushima|Kitakata City]], [[:en:Fukushima Prefecture|Fukushima Prefecture]], Japan.  

== Overview ==  
The group comprises one {{ill|Square Kofun|ja|方墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|qq=}} (方墳, hōfun) and three {{ill|Keyhole-shaped kofun|ja|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}}. They are believed to have been constructed during the early [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]. The kofun were likely built by a third prominent clan in the Aizu Basin, following the clans that constructed the {{ill|Ikki Kofun Group|ja|一箕古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikki Kofun Group|qq=}} and the {{ill|Unai Aotsu Kofun Group|ja|宇内青津古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unai Aotsu Kofun Group|qq=}}.  

== Kofun in the Group ==  
* '''Fukasawa Kofun'''  
* '''Tanaka Funamori-yama Kofun'''  
* '''Jūkyūdan Kofun'''  
* '''Kannommori Kofun'''  

== References ==  
* Hidehito Tsuji, *"The Origin of Tohoku Kofun Research: Aizu Otsukayama Kofun"* (Series: *Learning from Sites* 029), Shinseisha, 2006  
